60\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\lang1033\cgrid {\fs28 \par \par }{\b\fs28 1. Overview}{\fs28 \par The aim of this project is the development and deployment of an Observation Simulator for the Large-aperture Synoptic Survey Telescope (LSST). The Simulator should be able to operate as a standalone application.\par \par \par }{\b\fs28 2. Requirements}{\fs28 \par Requirements for the Simulator can be divided into two categories: operational requirements and technical requirements. The former group deals, roughly speaking, with "what the Simulator is supposed to do". The latter, with "how the Simulator is supposed to do it".\par \par }{\b\fs28 2.1. Operational Requirements\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 1.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-720\li1440\nowidctlpar\tx720\jclisttab\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\faauto\ls1\rin0\lin1440\itap0 {\fs28 The Simulator should be able to schedule up to TBD exposures per night.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 2.\tab}The Simulator should make sure that the allocation of telescope time is such that, on average (over one year), each science program matches its science goals.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 3.\tab}The Simulator should schedule observations in order to satisfy the cadence requirements of the science programs.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 4.\tab}The Simulator should be able to schedule observations up to a time scale comparable to the shortest cadence allowed by the telescope.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 5.\tab}The Simulator should not schedule observations closer than TBD degrees to the Sun or to the Moon.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 6.\tab}}{\fs28 The Simulator should not schedule observations}{\fs28  in user-defined exclusion zones.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 7.\tab}The Simulator should be able to take the current seeing conditions into account in determining the scheduling of observations of the different science programs.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 8.\tab}The Simulator should take the current airmass into consideration in determining the scheduling of observations of the different science programs.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 9.\tab}The Simulator should take the current weather conditions into consideration in determining the scheduling of observations of the different science programs.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 10.\tab}The Simulator should take the expected image depth into consideration in determining the scheduling of observations of the different science programs.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 11.\tab}The Simulator should take into consideration:\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 a.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-720\li2160\nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\jclisttab\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\faauto\ls1\ilvl1\rin0\lin2160\itap0 {\fs28 The pointing limits of the telescope.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 b.\tab}Telescope slewing time.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 c.\tab}Telescope settling time.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 d.\tab}Dome rotation speed.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 e.\tab}Shutter time.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 f.\tab}Readout time of the camera.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 g.\tab}Exposure time.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 h.\tab}Configuration change time (filters etc.).\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 i.\tab}Engineering time.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 j.\tab}Down time.\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs28 \par \par }{\b\fs28 2.2. Technical Requirements}{\fs28 \par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 1.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-720\li1440\nowidctlpar\tx720\jclisttab\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\faauto\ls2\rin0\lin1440\itap0 {\fs28 Users should be able to ingest their own (Phase 2) science proposals.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 2.\tab}Users should be able to use an arbitrary number of proposals.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 3.\tab}Users should be able to run the simulation for as long as they want.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 4.\tab}The Simulator should have efficient memory management.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 5.\tab}The Simulator should be responsive to user interaction.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 6.\tab}Users should be able to easily set and edit simulation parameters (e.g. FoV of the camera, latitude/longitude of the observatory, telescope slew time, dome rotation speed, filter switching times, weather data/model, exclusion zones etc.).\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 7.\tab}There should be no hard-coded minimum time step in the simulation.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 8.\tab}The code of the Simulator should be easy to modify by a non-expert developer.\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fs28 \hich\af4\dbch\af0\loch\f4 9.\tab}The Simulator should be adequately documented.\par }}